# Introduction

Tables provide presentation-focused layout for tabular data in documents. For typed data with column validation and structured datasets, see [datatables](./datatables.smd) which offer specialized styling and features for data-oriented use cases.

# Tokens

## Spacing Tokens

Control vertical separation and layout spacing for tables.

| Token                            | Description                                  | Default Value                        |
| -------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| `--table-spacing-top`            | Top margin (automatic responsive scaling)    | `var(--content-spacing)`             |
| `--table-spacing-bottom`         | Bottom margin (automatic responsive scaling) | `var(--content-spacing)`             |
| `--table-caption-spacing-bottom` | Gap between caption and table                | `calc(var(--content-spacing) * 0.5)` |
| `--table-notes-spacing-top`      | Gap between table and notes                  | `calc(var(--content-spacing) * 0.5)` |

